paragraphs.text:
%sql
CREATE OR REPLACE TEMPORARY VIEW VALID_TRIPS AS
select * from tripdata 
where Passenger_count between 1 and 5 
and Payment_type between 1 and 4 
and RateCodeID between 1 and 6
and tpep_pickup_datetime < tpep_dropoff_datetime
and trip_distance > 0
and  fare_amount > 0
and extra >= 0
and mta_tax  >= 0
and improvement_surcharge  >=  0
and tip_amount  >=  0
and  tolls_amount  >=  0
and total_amount  >=  0
and total_amount >= 0 
and tpep_pickup_datetime between  '2017-11-01 00:00:00.0' and '2018-01-01 00:00:00.0'
and tpep_dropoff_datetime between  '2017-11-01 00:00:00.0' and '2018-01-01 00:00:00.0'

paragraphs.title: Which is the most preferred mode of payment?
paragraphs.text:
%sql
select payment_type , count(1) count,

CASE
    WHEN payment_type = 1 THEN "Credit Card"
    WHEN payment_type = 2 THEN "Cash"
    WHEN payment_type = 3 THEN "No charge"
    WHEN payment_type = 4 THEN "Dispute"
    WHEN payment_type = 5 THEN "Unknown"
    ELSE "Void Trip"
END AS payment_type_description

paragraphs.title: Segregate the data into five segments of ‘tip paid’: [0-5), [5-10), [10-15) , [15-20) and >=20. Calculate the percentage share of each bucket (i.e. the fraction of trips falling in each bucket).
paragraphs.text:
%sql
select (count(1) / (select count(1) from VALID_TRIPS)) *100 trips_percentage,
CASE
    WHEN tip_amount between 0 and 4.999 THEN "[0-5)"
    WHEN tip_amount between 5 and 9.999 THEN  "[5-10)"
    WHEN tip_amount between 10 and 14.999 THEN  "[10-15)"
    WHEN tip_amount between 15 and 19.999 THEN  "[15-20)"
    WHEN tip_amount >= 20 THEN ">=20"
    ELSE "Invalid"
END AS tip_class

from VALID_TRIPS
group by tip_class

paragraphs.title: Analyse the average speed of the most happening days of the year, i.e. 31st December (New year’s eve) and 25th December (Christmas Eve) and compare it with the overall average.
paragraphs.text:
%sql
select 
    to_date(tpep_pickup_datetime) `Date`,
    count(1) trips_count,
    avg(trip_distance * 3600 /(unix_timestamp(tpep_dropoff_datetime) - unix_timestamp(tpep_pickup_datetime))) `avg_speed (miles/hr)`,
    
    CASE
        WHEN to_date(tpep_pickup_datetime) = "2017-12-25" THEN "Christmas Eve"
        WHEN to_date(tpep_pickup_datetime) = "2017-12-31" THEN "New year’s eve"
        ELSE "normal days"
    END AS occasion
    
     
    
    from VALID_TRIPS 
    
    where tpep_pickup_datetime between '2017-12-31 00:00:00.0' and '2018-01-01 00:00:00.0' 
    or  tpep_pickup_datetime between '2017-12-25 00:00:00.0' and '2017-12-26 00:00:00.0' 
    group by to_date(tpep_pickup_datetime)
